reckless. traffic rules are practiced half-halfheartedly and rarely if ever enforced. zebra crossings are for display, cars are allowed to turn right on a red light and rarely stop for pedestrians. biker tend to do as they like. don't be fooled by following any signs and pedestrian paths; it is very common to see a motorcycle driving in a pedestrian lane. on occasion even cars will take to bike lanes and motor bikes to the sidewalk. equally, pedestrians often walk in the roadways, especially at night, as they are better lit. look in all directions when crossing! expect or assume 